    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Piping or tubing in coils, spirals, or other various configurations, employed in cooling or heating systems to serve as heat exchangers. For the any general object genre designed as concentric rings or circles, use "coils (object genre)."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000010761/Harris, Dictionary of Architecture and Construction (1975)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Cañerias o tuberias en varias configuraciones empleadas en sistemas de enfriamiento o calefacción para servir como intercambiador de calor.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
